===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sūþ]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# One of the four major [[compass point]]s, specifically 180°, directed toward the [[South Pole]], and conventionally [[downwards]] on a map.
# {{figurative}} The [[down]] or [[negative]] direction.
#: ''His luck turned '''south'''.''
#: ''The water numbed everything '''south''' of my ribcage.''

